The paper focuses on evaluating the effectiveness of vulnerability detection tools for Android apps, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The evaluation also involves empirical testing, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing tools and the need for more rigorous evaluations, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG).
